Dear Actors, 

Join me Saturday for a free 75-minute ONLINE class: HOW TO CHOOSE A MONOLOGUE FOR ANY AUDITION.  Participants can read or perform monologues for feedback  and I cover a LOT about choosing monologues, including . . .

‚Ä¢ How to find material that‚Äôs great for you
‚Ä¢ Where to look
‚Ä¢ How to recognize good material
‚Ä¢ Choosing well for specific kinds of auditions
‚Ä¢ Building a killer repertoire
‚Ä¢ Effective cutting and editing
‚Ä¢ When and when not to do overdone monologues
‚Ä¢ The ‚ÄúHello, This Is Me‚Äù monologue and why it‚Äôs so incredibly valuable for auditioning actors

To reserve, email classes@monologueaudition.com

**Can't do this one? Email classes@monologueaudition.com to join my list and hear about next classes and free events :) **

You can also visit my website, MonologueAudition.com for Monologue FAQ, Monday Morning Monologues (free feedback on Mondays), a short film about how I teach monologues, and much more :) 

~Karen 

KAREN KOHLHAAS is a director and founding ensemble member of the Atlantic Theater Company and senior teacher at the Atlantic Acting School. She teaches her own online classes in monologues, cold reading, scene study, and directing, and is the author of The Monologue Audition: A Practical Guide for Actors (recommended by Helen Mirren in her Master Class on acting, and a Backstage must-read); and How to Choose a Monologue for Any Audition. She was named Best NYC Monologue Teacher and Best NYC Cold Reading Teacher by Backstage readers.

We're on the lookout for a jolly, warm-hearted Father Christmas to bring festive magic to life at one of Liverpool‚Äôs top attractions this November & December!

‚ú® The Role: You‚Äôll be the star of our magical grotto experience, meeting families, chatting with children, and spreading Christmas cheer. A twinkle in the eye, a hearty "Ho Ho Ho", and a love of all things festive are a must!

URGENT!

Looking for a red rose bouquet for a bridal shoot in London on Saturday 27th September! 

Must be local to E17 for pickup or be able to get to Cannon Street Station at 7am for collection. 

Our florist has unfortunately had an issue with her flowers and can no longer deliver. 

Also looking for a videographer to work alongside the photographer capturing BTS and various videos of the model. Please note the videos must be delivered on the same day due to time constraints. The videos can be taken on a phone with high quality video. 

TFP

Series - September 2025
Rejoinder: 5.5 - Script Breakdown: Identify Chemical Messengers

At the prompting of the brain, the sensory system (the five senses) import raw data (script) from the external environment (stage) into the internal environment. At the prompting of the brain, the mind synthesizes stimuli from the raw data received. At the prompting of the brain, the limbic system generates emotions in response to the synthesized stimuli. At the prompting of the brain, the skeletal and muscular systems express emotions as human behavior (dramatic performance).

At the prompting of the brain, chemical messengers facilitate or inhibit the transition of information between body parts. The release of chemical messengers operate in auto mode in real life situation, because the host human body has the internal intelligence base to facilitate it. It gets tricky in a dramatic performance situation in which the actor plays a character role. The actor delivers poor quality dramatic performance because she lacks the intelligence base capacity to the release process of chemical messengers. Just like sophisticated Artificial Intelligence (AI) processes require huge amount of electrical power to execute, chemical messengers require 'super duper' high quality intelligence base to process. If the actor could identify the chemical messengers required for a proposed dramatic performance, she could build up the necessary intelligence base to support it.

What do you think? This is a scientific approach to acting. I welcome a discussion for a better understanding. Feel free to express yourself with a question or a statement. There is so much to explore, thinking outside the box.

Note: Send me a message to join my subscription-based virtual scientific acting class.

Connor Knowles is a passionate model and actor based in Derby, United Kingdom. With a background in social media. Hosting boxing events, and promoting, he has developed a versatile skill set that allows him to thrive in both the modelling and acting realms. 

Having currently not worked with any clothing brands but looking to work with many brands and appearing in projects such as Rise of the Footsoldier: Retribution as a supporting actor, and recently featured in a YouTube video for the content creator MystroYNL in a video called ‚ÄúGuess the Black Person‚Äù, he is known for his ability to bring characters to life with authenticity and grace. He‚Äôs always looking to work with anyone and further develop his character and personal brand. 

In addition to his modelling and acting work, Connor Knowles is very versatile and talented and has the ability to create a unique style and personality to his work, which enhances his performances. When not in front of the camera, he enjoys creating content on social media, promoting his work, and sharing his creativity with others. While also engaging in his own personal creative ventures which reflect on his vibrant personality. 

For inquiries, please contact via connorleeknowles04@gmail.com or his social media handles @CKnowlesUK/@CKnowlesUK_

**Frequent, flexible work opportunities for confident, professional performers with a highly popular Children's entertainment company. We need Seasonal Santa, Party Hosts, Princess Performers **

**Pay: ¬£30- ¬£50 per hour depending on role and responsibilities**

At Bunny Business Events, it is coming up to our busiest time of the year and due to high demand we need to expand our team! We are looking for confident performers, party hosts, performing arts students, actors, singers and those who love working with Children. We are expanding our Santa team (candidates need to be age appropriate for this role), princess performers and generic party hosts. We have frequent & consistent part time work available. Our events are located within Greater Manchester, South Manchester, Warrington and Cheshire. Your residence needs to be within comfortable travelling distance of SK9 Postcode.

**If you are interested in applying please contact with your CV and headshot to hello@bunnybusinessevents.co.uk**

Bunny Business - **Social Media Page**

Bunny Business is one of the leading Children's entertainment companies in the North West. With multiple event's a week, ranging from superheroes, princesses, mascots and disco's, we are now looking for reliable, outgoing children's entertainers to join our team!

So what's the gig? Well, you will receive frequent, flexible bookings during weekend, seasonal events and school holidays, hosting and entertaining large groups of children at various different locations. You will be celebrating birthdays, christenings, Easter, Halloween and Christmas events as well as weddings and corporates. All equipment and training is provided by Bunny Business. It is also advantageous if you can represent one of our many characters, whether it be a superhero, princess or a mascot, all of which are provided by us. This role is perfect if you are looking for additional, flexible income to support your current work commitments.

You need to have the ability to command the attention of the room! You will be responsible for ensuring the smooth running of events and parties, providing excellent hospitality and guest services whilst in character.

***To apply you must have the following set of qualities***

* Confident, loud, fun, engaging, humorous and entertaining
* Frequent Weekend availability
* Must drive and provide own transport (travel cost subsidised)
* Must be able to work in a fast-paced environment with multiple interruptions for attention.
* Provide the highest standard of customer service to our clients
* Strong time management skills

**Experience:-** 

* Previous experience in hospitality, performing arts and/or dance or event management is advantageous
* Strong interpersonal skills with the ability to interact with guests of all ages
* Excellent organisational skills to manage multiple tasks effectively
* Ability to work in a fast-paced environment while maintaining a positive attitude
*  A passion for creating enjoyable experiences for guests

This self employed opportunity is fantastic if you are looking for flexible additional income that is lucrative, engaging, fun and inspiring. Join us as a Party Host or seasonal character and be part of a dynamic team dedicated to delivering exceptional guest experiences.

items.title: Let's welcome our new members!

items.text:
Dear Actors,

Join me Saturday for a free 75-minute ONLINE class: HOW TO CHOOSE A MONOLOGUE FOR ANY AUDITION. Participants can read or perform monologues for feedback and I cover a LOT about choosing monologues, including . . .

‚Ä¢ How to find material that‚Äôs great for you

‚Ä¢ Where to look

‚Ä¢ How to recognize good material

‚Ä¢ Choosing well for specific kinds of auditions

‚Ä¢ Building a killer repertoire

‚Ä¢ Effective cutting and editing

‚Ä¢ When and when not to do overdone monologues

‚Ä¢ The ‚ÄúHello, This Is Me‚Äù monologue and why it‚Äôs so incredibly valuable for auditioning actors

To reserve, email classes@monologueaudition.com

**Can't do this one? Email classes@monologueaudition.com to join my list and hear about next classes and free events **

You can also visit my website, [MonologueAudition.com](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2FMonologueAudition.com%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExUGxxbEZsY25xaHBoSW40cAEeJzUpxoxkk8IAGuoXPed2dpCcRlheOjjgRAVP00mfdDVBvK5y1Y7p5erSZwM_aem_y_JjjeKhXDzAd4gL3o_YpA&h=AT2SzwNGUcfseY8U5jbSJtVfIRwE_g22k5WVERgxbqaIczjJipVN2sjX-fb7_zPTLCnyy5oG67DtMyxbimdfsGRBNgkmtLyOa6PtTzgM-HehzSyWaHMhm4IcoMEj3sZr1pm2ZzDpIPD7kCJ4WIw&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT1w7WODxybGNsi9BrryNcYumKH_PlfNt4DutYT-Ra8kNWBJgkBFucjbjW2s93nUrkh4_PoOXx-2ugUw2kfhAsNrGqWib2RKcFea8LCuF9FZH1YOJ1ETVkHqDhxdaoh0RvdF6rbsqGnAwF8icjRgnG-3f1qaAcghrrXV0fn8NHHRZhQvqu2XbuLeQzijbw4hyOS_SiZhWo6vYHou3W2bVeEi86nSgHgqNGK29Rp_PqlDNBy1GOoz) for Monologue FAQ, Monday Morning Monologues (free feedback on Mondays), a short film about how I teach monologues, and much more

~Karen

KAREN KOHLHAAS is a director and founding ensemble member of the Atlantic Theater Company and senior teacher at the Atlantic Acting School. She teaches her own online classes in monologues, cold reading, scene study, and directing, and is the author of The Monologue Audition: A Practical Guide for Actors (recommended by Helen Mirren in her Master Class on acting, and a Backstage must-read); and How to Choose a Monologue for Any Audition. She was named Best NYC Monologue Teacher and Best NYC Cold Reading Teacher by Backstage readers.

items.text:
CASTING CALL

We‚Äôre looking for a female actor to join us this December for our RAPUNZEL pantomime (school tour). 

We‚Äôre casting either of the following parts, with our existing performer playing the opposite role. 

- Rapunzel (lead)
- Gothel (villain)

Last year was our best selling tour - but we hope to beat that this year! Because it‚Äôs schools, the shows are weekday mornings and early afternoons, so you‚Äôll have your evenings and weekends free. The performances are in the Norfolk, Suffolk and Cambridge area. 

We‚Äôre currently offering a minimum of ¬£870 - which will go up as we get more bookings in + travel expenses. 
The tour spans from 1st - 19th December 2025. 
Aiming to start weekly rehearsals asap - in Hunstanton (PE36). These are unpaid but we keep them as flexible as possible.

This will be our thirteenth panto tour, and we‚Äôve built up a good name in the area, with schools booking us year after year (even before we announce the title!) We pride ourselves on being a warm, friendly, but professional company.

If interested, please get in touch for further details - either by a PM on here, or via email - purple-dreams@hotmail.co.uk - I‚Äôm looking forward to hearing from (some of) you üôÇ

Many thanks
Tobias Nicholls
Creative Director 
Purple Dreams Productions

items.text:
INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

items.title: Hello,

items.text:

items.text:
Female Host ‚Äì Horror/True Crime Talk Show
Location: Burbank, California (or surrounding areas)

We are seeking a dynamic female host to join our on-camera team for a horror and true crime‚Äìfocused web series. This role requires someone with strong on-screen presence, a passion for horror, true crime, and the supernatural, and the ability to engage with both co-hosts and guests in a lively, authentic way.

Responsibilities:
 ‚Ä¢ Co-host alongside two main hosts during live-taped shows.
 ‚Ä¢ Contribute knowledge and insights on horror, true crime, and supernatural subjects.
 ‚Ä¢ Engage with guests, audience members, and co-hosts with energy and professionalism.
 ‚Ä¢ Help shape conversations that are informative, entertaining, and on-brand.

Requirements:
 ‚Ä¢ Female host talent based in Burbank, California, or nearby areas.
 ‚Ä¢ Strong knowledge of horror, true crime, and supernatural genres.
 ‚Ä¢ Confident on-camera presence and strong improvisational/conversational skills.
 ‚Ä¢ Ability to work collaboratively with other hosts.
 ‚Ä¢ Must be available for scheduled back-to-back tapings.
 ‚Ä¢ We are especially interested in candidates who already have a horror-style look or aesthetic that fits the tone of the show.

Compensation & Perks:
 ‚Ä¢ $500 per show.
 ‚Ä¢ We film two shows back-to-back per shoot day.
 ‚Ä¢ If selected, we will privately share details of the show and company.
 ‚Ä¢ All employees receive a quarterly bonus based on the show‚Äôs performance.
 ‚Ä¢ Small, tight-knit crew where every team member receives a percentage of the show‚Äôs profits.
 ‚Ä¢ Immediate hire.

How to Apply:

Please submit the following materials:
 ‚Ä¢ Headshot (highlighting your look and style).
 ‚Ä¢ Demo reel or on-camera sample (hosting, acting, or relevant video work).
 ‚Ä¢ Resume with relevant experience.
 ‚Ä¢ A brief note on why you‚Äôre passionate about horror/true crime/supernatural.

Submit to VCSales505@gmail.com

**Casting Call - Cornwall based Talent **

I'm producing a suite of social ads for a food hamper brand and casting talent for photography and video assets. 

We are looking to replicate people from all walks of life, celebrating the sweet life moments with a range of hamper gifts.

**Talent Requirements**
* Between 30 and 50
* Any gender, race, ability.
* Must have basic modelling and basic experience
* These are non speaking roles, but you must be comfortable acting out sequences, such as receiving a gift, opening the door to a package, etc.

**Please note: applicants MUST be based in the South Cornwall area and within a reasonable commute from our location in Praa Sands. **

**Filming: **Praa Sands, Thursday 16th October.  Beach front home location.

**Payment**

**Pays ¬£350 for the day **(this fee includes the BSF and 1 year usage for paid social and web use)

Travel expenses up to ¬£20 (with valid travel receipts), light breakfast and lunch is covered. 

**Please email giorgia@nusastudios.com **with your portfolio and headshot.

Thanks so much

Giorgia

üì¢Volunteers Wanted - Videographers! Liverpool Mystery Eventüì¢

CAJ Productions is looking for 2 more reliable volunteers to help with a one-off mystery stunt in Liverpool City Centre on Saturday 20th September 2025.

It's part of a brand-new UK theatre tour coming in 2026, and this will be one of our headline public marketing stunts. 

The role is simple, but really important:

. Filming the event (reactions) on a phone (2 people required)

What you'll get:

. Travel expenses covered

. Be part of an unusual, exciting event that's going to get a lot of attention

. Something different to talk about (and looks great on a CV for anyone in events, film, or theatre)

If you're free, reliable, and up for being part of something mysterious and fun, drop me a message here or comment below and I'll share the details.

Thanks! 

Charlie

Hi all, (apologies if this isn‚Äôt the right place for my post)

Im new to this and never had the opportunity to try and pursue it until now due to multiple factors over the years.

I‚Äôm 39 and looking to really make something of acting but currently have zero experience, however looking to gain as much as possible. I‚Äôm on NE14 but they never get back to you and they always look for specifics that I don‚Äôt fit into - could be a certain height, no tattoos, certain build etc 

Like I say I‚Äôm new to all of this with zero experience but would like any and all opportunities to help me make something of it üòä and I will put my ALL into it!! 

Thanks

items.text:
Casting Call - Vancouver BC

Non-Union

Shoot Dates: October (TBD)

Rate: $200 (one day shoot)

Location: Vancouver BC, Kerrisdale.

ROLE:

[Male Lead]

Age: 27-38

Ethnicity: Any

Gender: Man

Callbacks and Rehearsal: Zoom. 

Tone: Grounded and realistic. (e.g Normal People on Prime)

We are seeking a male lead for a one-day location shoot in Kerrisdale for our proof of concept short film. The actor should be comfortable with intimate conversations and improv; open to collaborating during rehearsal to complete the script as we are looking for a very natural and realistic dialogue. 

 TO SUBMIT and RECEIVE AUDITION SIDES: Please send your name, contact info, recent photos or headshots and availability to: [mariajulianakidmoro@gmail.com]

Thanks! Maria and Gabi.

items.text:
**Paid Studio Gig ‚Äì Surrey, BC (1‚Äì2 days, max 7 hrs/day)**

Hey Vancouver actors! We‚Äôre producing a batch of short videos for our brand (YouTube, Reels, TikTok, Facebook) and are looking for a confident on-camera presenter to record with us at our Surrey studio.

**What it is:**
* 1‚Äì2 studio days, max **7 hours per day**
* Scripted teleprompter reads + a few simple pickups/B-roll
* We provide the studio, teleprompter, and all gear
* **Contract provided** and **payment in full on wrap**

**You:** Comfortable on camera, friendly, clear delivery, can self-report to Surrey.

**Dates/Rate:** negotiable and flexable 

If you‚Äôre interested, please fill out this form, https://form.jotform.com/252610493666057 

with:
* Headshot + reel/links
* Your availability in **[date range]**
* A quick note confirming you can get to Surrey

Thanks! Excited to meet some local talent.

items.text:
Tickets are now available for our upcoming Actors and Filmmakers Networking Event, taking place on Sunday, October 26th.

 

Networking is essential for advancing your career in the industry, and Marble Academy for Drama and Management has proudly facilitated these events for years. With over 90 attendees, our June gathering was a tremendous success, and we are determined to build on that momentum.

 

You will have the opportunity to engage with accomplished actors, visionary directors, prominent producers, and skilled crew members who can offer valuable insights and possibly help bring your next project to life.

 

Think about it, if there were an event where you could connect with exceptionally talented cast and crew who could help bring your next project to life, wouldn‚Äôt you want to be there?

 

Take a look at this video from a previous event‚Ä¶..

www.youtube.com/watch?v=EM4jwjRxny4

 

So, join us on Sunday, October 26th, from 2 PM to 6:30 PM at HOME Mcr, located at 2 Tony Wilson Place, Manchester, M15 4FN.

 

Secure your tickets through this link:

www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239

 

I look forward to seeing you there!

** **

Whether you're just starting or want to improve the talent you already have, Marble Academy in Swinton, Manchester, will help unlock your full potential and refine your craft to help capture the attention of casting directors in film, television, and theatre.

 

Here‚Äôs why you should seize this incredible opportunity:

**Renowned Excellence**: Marble Academy is not only celebrated by Spotlight as one of the premier drama academies in the country, but is also the recipient of the **Manchester & North West Prestige Awards **for **Theatre School Of The Year**.
Here, you won‚Äôt just learn; you‚Äôll train with one of the best in the business!

 

**Authentic Training**: Our L.A.M.D.A.-qualified tutor, Christian Le Feuvre, brings a wealth of real-world experience that empowers you to delve deeply into characters and scenes. His insightful feedback doesn‚Äôt just boost your confidence; it ignites your growth as an actor, providing you with a fresh perspective on every script. With his nurturing and constructive coaching style, you‚Äôll be amazed at how he can transform your journey as an actor.

 

But don‚Äôt just take our word for it‚Äîexplore the glowing reviews and dive into our programme details for a closer look at what we offer at www.marbleacademy.co.uk

 

Audition dates are still available!

items.text:
The first 10 mins of my first full length play Blackout 1985 is going to be performed as part of Wooden Arrow Productions next scratch evening on 30th October at Lamda at their Sainsburys Theatre!

The casting is UNPAID but there will be professional photography, industry guests for feedback and a chance to network after with the guests and the audience. There are also other roles in other plays that need filling. 

Deadline is this Saturday!

Synopsis of Blackout 1985: 28th September 1985. A day marked in history. The Lewis family gathers in their living room as the streets outside erupt in flames. Winston and Angie strive to protect their children, Jimmy and Asha, from a world that denies their humanity. As generational wounds, dreams, and tensions collide, the family must decide whether to stay safe behind closed doors or step into the fire of history. Blackout 1985 is the first in the trilogy, which shines a light on key Black British moments.

If you are interested or know anyone please go to this link - https://forms.gle/uJFMiQzyR6kVqBae8

Competitive salary, flights and accommodation provided.

**Hola Everyone,**

I‚Äôm a SAG-AFTRA actor, director, and coach with 25+ years in this business. You might‚Äôve seen me in *Cry Macho*, *Minority Report*, *War of the Worlds*, *American Horror Story*, *Sons of Anarchy*, *NCIS: LA*, or as Marc Molina on *The Secret Life of the American Teenager*. items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‚Äò Habeus Corpus‚Äô by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett‚Äôs Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the Ô¨Çat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall
Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 
Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.
Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 
The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

items.text:
Hey everyone my name is Manraj Heer I‚Äôm the producer for our student short film at Vancouver Film School. The film is called ‚ÄúBeginnings‚Äù and we are shooting on October 11th & 12th, 2025. We are currently looking to hire three male actors. For the roles of Athan, Hooded Man, and Rick. If you are interested please send your resume, headshot, and any demo reel to teambeginnings@gmail.com and we will reach out to you for a self tape to help narrow down the process.

The deadline for demo tapes and applications end on October 3rd, 2025. So please get in your application at your earliest convenience.

Synopsis:
Athan celebrates his 21st birthday surrounded by the people he loves the most. Family and
friends cheer for the start of a new phase of Athan‚Äôs life. A new beginning. Until time suddenly
stops. Everyone freezing in place, except for Athan, who knows the memory has ended.
Guided by a Hooded Man, an older and wiser version of himself, Athan must find purpose by
visiting rooms in a seemingly never-ending hallway, each filled with crucial moments of his life
‚Äî learning the role of the people that surround him (and the impact he has on them), dealing
with love in an ever-transforming relationship, and embracing grief from the never-stopping
passage of time.
After impulsively deciding to skip entering the rest of the doors out of agony, Athan will find
how quickly a lifetime goes by ‚Äî but be ready to accept his new chapter behind a final, bright room.

CASTING BREAKDOWN ‚Äì VANCOUVER FILM SCHOOL
Project Title: Beginnings
Project Type: Student Short Film
Union Status: Non-Union
Director: J. D. Estevez
Producer: Raj Heer / Vancouver Film School
Casting Director: Manraj Heer, J. D. Estevez
Audition Dates: Self-tapes due by October 3rd, 2025
Audition Location: Self-tapes only
Call Back Dates: October 4th, 2025
Call Back Location: 142 Water Street, Vancouver, BC V6B 1B2
Shooting Dates: October 11th ‚Äì 12th, 2025
Shooting Location: Greater Vancouver Area
Rates: Unpaid. Catering and craft service provided.
Submission Instructions: Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel
to teambeginnings@gmail.com and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for.

ATHAN / MALE / AGE : 20-25 / ANY ETHNICITY 

Na√Øve and foolish, Athan thinks he knows what he wants from life and what it is to be expected of him ‚Äî learning soon enough that you can never be prepared for what is behind
the next door. Though he is slow to realize the importance of every moment, and too clumsy
to show it, Athan is a deeply caring and empathetic person. He is willing to push everything
out of his way to spend more time with someone he loves. Despite repeatedly stumbling
through the hallway of life, Athan is motivated by a constant search for meaning.

HOODED MAN / MALE / AGE : 50-60 / ANY ETHNICITY
After living as a rebellious young Athan, the Hooded Man walks through the hallway of his life
once again. This time, he reflects on his past, accepting it for what it is, knowing he cannot
change it. Melancholic and somewhat regretful, he guides Athan, emphasizing the
importance of embracing every stage of life, whether joyful or somber. Unlike his younger
self, the Hooded Man moves deliberately through every memory, without hurry, but with
peace. Though seemingly stoic, there is a hint of disturbance behind his expression.

RICK / MALE / AGE : 40-50 / ANY ETHNICITY
Athan‚Äôs father, Rick, is a troubled man. He learned from his family to hide his true feelings and
often relies on bad habits to forget his past mistakes. He was able to distance himself from his
vices when he found a sense of purpose, such as when he married his childhood friend,
Emma. However, it didn't last long. Overwhelmed by regret and fearing that he won‚Äôt make
the most of his life, Rick sees Athan as a chance to start over. He is determined to ensure that
his son won't make the same mistakes he did. However, with his marriage falling apart and
Athan soon becoming independent, Rick can‚Äôt help but start drinking again.

 Look forward to seeing everyone‚Äôs submissions! If you have any questions or concerns please reach me at teambeginnings@gmail.com.

The first 10 mins of my first full length play Blackout 1985 is going to be performed as part of Wooden Arrow Productions next scratch evening on 30th October at Lamda at their Sainsburys Theatre!

The casting is UNPAID but there will be professional photography, industry guests for feedback and a chance to network after with the guests and the audience. There are also other roles in other plays that need filling. 

Deadline is this Saturday!

Synopsis of Blackout 1985: 28th September 1985. A day marked in history. The Lewis family gathers in their living room as the streets outside erupt in flames. Winston and Angie strive to protect their children, Jimmy and Asha, from a world that denies their humanity. As generational wounds, dreams, and tensions collide, the family must decide whether to stay safe behind closed doors or step into the fire of history. Blackout 1985 is the first in the trilogy, which shines a light on key Black British moments.

If you are interested or know anyone please go to this link - 
https://forms.gle/uJFMiQzyR6kVqBae8

Please read carefully below for details:

DETAILS:
- Project: 'OHIO JOBS' Promotional Shoot
- Project Location: Cleveland, OH (TBD) / Columbus, OH (TBD) / Cincinnati, OH (TBD)
- Date(s): October 7th / October 8th / October 9th / October 10th
- CALLBACK Date: Tuesday, September 30th (via Zoom)
- Rate: $500/10hr +20% per Session.
- Fitting Rate: $50/hr + 20% 
(Cincinnati Talent will fit on OCTOBER 6th. Columbus & Cleveland Talent will fit ON-SET)
- Usage: 2-Year Usage Buyout $2500 + 20% (Broadcast, Digital, Social, Print, OOH, Industrial)

WHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR:
WE HAVE 18 ROLES OVER THE 3 OHIO CITIES FOR ALL AGES AND ETHNICITIES!!

Link to Roles & Cities they film: https://bit.ly/OhioJobsROLESandCITIES

SUBMISSION / AUDITION INSTRUCTIONS:
- Please email all auditions to: angela@angelaboehmcasting.com

- Deadline for Auditions is 9:00am on FRIDAY, SEPTEMBER 26th.

- SUBJECT LINE: OHIO JOBS Audition / (Your Name)
- Please have a blank background (DO NOT film outside).
- Please slate at the end of the audition (Slate can be in a separate video).

Slate Requirements:
- Full Name
- Agent (Phone number if you do not have an Agent)
- Location (PLEASE SLATE IF YOU'RE WILLING TO WORK LOCAL IN MORE THAN ONE OF THE MENTIONED CITIES)
- Please include in your slate a close-up of BOTH of your hands, FRONT & BACK!
- PLEASE SLATE ANY CONFLICTS ON FILMING/FITTING/CALLBACK DATES
- Please send the audition via Dropbox Folder or via WeTransfer Link (PLEASE MAKE SURE WE HAVE PERMISSION TO OPEN YOUR FILE).

Click below for the Audition Sides:
Link to Sides: https://bit.ly/OhioJobsSIDES

Kind regards,
Angela Boehm Casting Team

PLEASE NOTE: This is just a submission. If you are booked, we will reach out to YOU.

**$500 Finders Fee: Have You Been Ghosted By Your Husband Or Wife? (Docu-Series Casting)**

An acclaimed television production company and a major cable network are actively searching for women and men whose spouse has suddenly and mysteriously vanished, without warning, without explanation, and with no way to contact them. If you are still *legally married* but don‚Äôt know *where *your spouse is, you don‚Äôt have a clear explanation or *‚Äúwhy‚Äù* they left, or *how* to reach them, *we want to hear your story for a bold and empowering new series.*

**$500 Referral Fee: **Do You Know Someone? Share their information with us or simply have them tell us you referred them! Finders fee is paid IF referral is selected for production. 

*Selected for series candidates are compensated for taking part as well as receive expert help in tracking down their missing spouse, rebuilding their lives and finding closure. *

**To apply, please email: ****[casting@bodegapictures.com](mailto:casting@bodegapictures.com)****, **or visit: https://abandonedspouseshortapp.castingcrane.com/

message.text: A little adventure for the soul! Feed your passions and live life it‚Äôs not always pretty but on this day it was at an elevation of 14,115 ft at the Summit of Pikes Peak in Colorado. Airs a little thin and I‚Äôm thicker than a snicker üòÜ I will forever love these types of viewpoints they recharge my spirit and humble me to see how small we are in the bigger picture. Beautiful red granite everywhere even brought home a few pieces ü§ì‚ù§Ô∏è I‚Äôm weird like that! This place is actually very accessible with car or tram. Great place to visit when near Denver or Colorado Springs. #pikespeak #colorado #summit #mountaintops #clouds #elevation #pikes #peak #adventure #travel #fun #soul #recharge #clearmymind #love #earth #places #mothernature #outdoors #redgranite #tram #co #dreambig
